    "updated_at": "2015-01-07T18:20:55Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "We generally prefer not to implement in-place operations unless there are clear performance benefits because they can lead to confusing behavior, especially with chained operations. For example `df['column'].do_something_inplace()` modifies the series `df['column']` --- and not, necessarily, the original dataframe `df`.\n"
  },
